267.character: 僕　ワルだから 過去は　振り返らないの
267.definition: I'm a bad guy, so I don't look at my past. Can I get a café mocha?

270.speaker: SQUIRREL
270.character: 腹ごなしに　バレーボールやらない
270.definition: How about some volleyball to work off that food? Sure.

273.speaker: MASAKI
273.character: 何気に　本格的っすね
273.definition: It's more realistic than I thought.

274.speaker: SQUIRREL
274.character: じゃあ　ゲーム開始よ

276.speaker: SQUIRRELS
276.definition: Nice play! Ow! Okay, now I'm serious!

279.speaker: SQUIRRELS
279.definition: Yay! Nice play! So, how did things turn out with the Miss Penkos?

280.speaker: PENGUIN
280.character: 思い出させないでくれる
280.definition: Please don't remind me of that?

281.speaker: PENGUIN
281.character: カフェモカ　おかわり
281.definition: Can I get another café mocha?

282.speaker: PANDA
282.character: ペンギンさんも たまには　ブラック飲めば？
282.definition: Why don't you try the black coffee sometime, Mr. Penguin?

283.speaker: PENGUIN
283.character: これ以上 苦い思いはしたくないよ
283.definition: I don't need anymore bitterness in my life.

284.speaker: POLAR BEAR
284.character: はい　ブラック　サービスね
284.definition: Here you go, black coffee. It's on the house.

285.speaker: PENGUIN
285.definition: It's bitter, right? Oh, Mr. Tree Kangaroo.

287.speaker: SASAKO
287.character: いつも　お疲れさまです
287.definition: Thank you for all of your hard work.

288.speaker: POLAR BEAR
288.character: マサキくん　頑張ってる？
288.definition: Is Masaki working hard? Yeah. Well, he seems to have gotten in with the Red Squirrels.

289.speaker: SQUIRRELS
289.character: イエーイ　ストレート勝ち！
289.definition: Yay! Straight wins! O-One more time!

292.speaker: PENGUIN
292.character: まろやかで　あと味　スッキリ
292.definition: It's mild with a refreshing finish. Such a mediocre comment.

296.speaker: POLAR BEAR
296.character: グルメレポーター失格だね
296.definition: You'd fail as a gourmet reporter.

297.speaker: PENGUIN
297.definition: Hey, wait a minute. Mr. Penguin, when did you become a gourmet reporter?

300.speaker: PANDA
300.character: なってないのに レポーター気取りなの？
300.definition: So you aren't a reporter, but you're acting like one?

301.speaker: PANDA
301.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

303.speaker: PANDA
303.character: ツリーの上から見ると　ペンギンさんの人間性の小ささがよく見えるね
303.definition: We can really see how petty you are from the top of that tree.

304.speaker: PENGUIN
304.character: もっと　いろいろ見えるでしょう
304.definition: You can see a lot more besides that, can't you?

305.speaker: PANDA
305.character: じゃ　ツリーの上からペンギンさんの隠したい現実を見よう
305.definition: Then let's view the truth you want to hide from the top of the tree.

306.speaker: PENGUIN
306.character: 厳しんな言い方やめて

307.speaker: PENGUIN
307.character: 大体ツリー　ツリーって　ここどこ
307.definition: And why do you keep saying, "tree"? Where are we?

309.speaker: POLAR BEAR
309.character: 来週のしろくまカフェは

310.speaker: POLAR BEAR
310.character: ペンギンさん一人でお送りします
310.definition: will be presented to you with just Mr. Penguin.

311.speaker: PENGUIN
311.definition: We're all going to be there. Enjoy!
